                            <comment id="12706217" author="dreiss" created="Tue, 5 May 2009 21:49:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The test hangs for me when I run with this patch.  Can anyone else reproduce?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12706259" author="rush" created="Tue, 5 May 2009 23:58:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, that would make sense. The unpatched test has an unfortunate tendency to hang as well and the patch doesn&apos;t change any of that.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I guess there are 2 ways to approach this one. You could run it in a debugger and step through the new code and see that it does the right thing. That&apos;s what I did.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Or you could apply both patches from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-487&quot; title=&quot;ThreadManagerTests::blockTest errors&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-487&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-487&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, see that concurrency_test (mostly) runs, then apply this patch and see that nothing breaks. But you probably still need to step through it to convince yourself that it&apos;s right.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I hate dealing with software sometimes...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
